POSIX functions:
	fork, execve, dup2, wait/waitpid
	gai_strerror - converts to human readable error from API function getaddrinfo
	getaddrinfo - converts string literals to hints for creating an address for socket
	freeaddrinfo - free out the address structure used in getaddrinfo
	socketpair - replacement for pipe in forked process
	epoll - puts socket to monitor loop.
	bind - binds socket to addr:port;
	socket - creates socket from addr:port;
	listen - listens a socket;
	accept - opens new socket per client;

